{SOUTH cannot bid 2\H at his second turn; that would be 
Fourth Suit Forcing and wouldn't show the \H suit at all.

With a game-forcing two-suiter he jumps to 3\H instead. 
NORTH recognizes that SOUTH must hold five \Ss and bids the \S game.}

